News 1 KICKSTART SHOW

KICKSTART - The ACTIVE USER GROUP are holding their 3rd annual show  at  the
end of this month on Saturday 27th May. Kickstart spring in style by getting
down  to  Ottershaw  this Spring Bank Holiday and get  yourself  some  great
bargains for your Amiga from FORE-MATT Home Computing.  You could  also  get
lucky  with  some great prizes to be won in the draw as well as competitions
and  demonstrations by the group members.  For more information  go  now  to
http://kickstart.amiga.tm


News: New Layout

We've  had a slight change in layout this month and added some new  features
so you don't get bored with a plain old price list! Talking about boring, we
were  thinking about changing the Subject Title of this mailing  to  reflect
the  fact  that  we have expanded beyond a straight price  list.   Our  best
suggestion  so  far has been "Amiga Fore-Matt" which  I  must  admit  has  a
somewhat familiar ring to it! Tell us what you think to that or send us your
suggestion.

Anyway,  you will already have noticed our new contents feature which allows
you  to  see  where everything is going to appear so you can quickly  scroll
down to something of interest if you wish.  The CD and disk price lists have
switched places for those that want to quickly jump in and get a price, with
most of you mainly interested in the CD prices.

For some time now we have been providing a Game Chart to various print, disk
and web magazines and we have decided it may be of use to you as well so  we
have  now put it at the bottom of the mailing for those that are interested.
Also,   for the non-gamers we have a utility chart showing the best  selling
utilities in Europe through GTI.  All GTI chart items are available to order
from FORE-MATT Home Computing (an official GTI partner).

Finally,  our Nightlong build up and preview will soon be completed as  will
the game which will be the biggest game ever produced for the Amiga!

