Coming soon: NIGHTLONG

Year 2099

Progress continuously advances like an unstoppable giant of Steel. The flat
lives of people slowly fade inside jam-packed cities like Union, capital of
the new nation.

Everything lies in the grip of an eternal paralysis, predicated like gospel
from Multinational Corporations. Only those who belong to the elite have
learned about arts and sciences, matter and soul.

States are nothing but flags, soldiers defending a civilization that is not
civil
anymore. Cyberspace has made his appearance to save the citizens from
averyday reality. It is a virtual network, generated from the fusion of all
digital connections of the last millenium.

Many Multinationals see this non-existent space as an ideal resort for their
business meetings and research communities.

Cyberspace can offer you anything: leisure, travels, friends you never had
and dreams you never dreamt. Drugs are its natural organic brainchild.

Recently a company has announced the inauguration of its latest "Neural-
Navigation System", with a slogan that proclaims "full reality in virtual
experiences"...

The Last sunrays are gone now, and the warm breeze of June's night somehow
weakens the miasma that people here call air.

In the desolation of the Union Industrial Borderland, Joshua Reeve,
ex-lietenant of the military services, is silently waiting for the arrival
of his new client.

He's not here for the money anyway. It's just that an old debt has to be
paid
back.

His wait is interrupted by the landing manoeuvre of a luxurious Limousine,
the car of his former captain Hugh Martens. It is strange, the taste in your
mouth when you're going to meet the man who saved your life. It's like
savouring your own blood.

"Hi Hugh" Joshua gets into the limousine. The door automatically closes
after him.

"Joshua, it's been a long time..."

"Too long. What's the score?"

Nowadays Martens is Union City's mayor, but his popularity seems to be going
rapidly downhill. The reason is directly connected to the attacks of a group
of terrorists, who have targeted the most important industrial installations
in the city, including the Genesis Cryogenic Enterprise, who is no less than
Martens' electoral sponsor.
